Sentencas: The thin-film multilayer structure of the membrane-electrode assembly in a solid oxide fuel cell which involves a NiO/ZrO2:Y2O3 anode functional layer and a La0.6Sr0.4CoO3 cathode functional layer and also a bilayer ZrO2:Y2O3/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte is formed by magnetron sputtering onto a supporting NiO/ZrO2:Y2O3 anode.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The effect of the functional electrode layers involved in the structure of a solid oxide fuel cell on its efficiency is studied.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The volt-ampere characteristics of multilayer fuel cells are studied in the temperature range of 800-600 degrees C.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It is shown that the inclusion of a thin (600 nm thick) cathode functional layer into the structure of the membrane-electrode assembly enhances the fuel cell efficiency by reducing the polarization losses on electrodes.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the fuel cell with the cathode functional layer is 2290 and 500 mW/cm(2) at 800 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The simultaneous presence of anode and cathode functional layers is found to be unwelcome because gives rise to diffusion limitations on the anode.
Titulo: The Effect of Thin Functional Electrode Layers on Characteristics of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
